<section class="hero">
  <h1>Eleven for communities</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Clubs, teams, choirs, committees. One space for the whole community,
    groups inside it for everything else, and no algorithm between you and
    your members.
  </p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#get">Get Eleven</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://home.elevenmessenger.com">Create your space</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-group" aria-label="Why communities pick Eleven">
  <ul class="cards">
    <li>
      <h3>Open groups</h3>
      <p>
        Members find and join the groups inside your space themselves —
        match threads, socials, committee. No admin bottleneck.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Access levels</h3>
      <p>
        Members, coaches, committee. Some groups open to all, some behind a
        level. You decide who sees what.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Paid memberships</h3>
      <p>
        Paid community? Put a price on an access level and members
        subscribe, monthly or yearly, on a 90/10 split — 90 to you, 10
        keeps Eleven running. Paid into your own Stripe account.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>One link to join</h3>
      <p>
        Sign-up season is a link in the newsletter. No accounts, no forms,
        no app-store hunt — any browser works.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>Helpers on a schedule</h3>
      <p>
        &ldquo;Remind everyone about training on Thursdays.&rdquo; Set it
        once. Done.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3>No algorithm</h3>
      <p>
        Every message reaches every member. Nothing gets ranked, buried, or
        promoted.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    <a href="/features/">All the features &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="feature-group" aria-label="Pricing for communities">
  <h2>What it costs</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">
    Joining is always free. The space pays once, however many members join.
  </p>
  <div class="plans">
    <div class="plan">
      <h3>Free</h3>
      <span class="price">&euro;0</span>
      <p>
        Every feature. Up to three spaces, 1&nbsp;GB of photos and files
        each.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="plan featured">
      <h3>Community &amp; Friends</h3>
      <span class="price">&euro;4<small>/month</small></span>
      <p>
        10&nbsp;GB of storage, never tidied away as unused.
      </p>
      <span class="alt">or &euro;40/year</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="fine" style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    Membership fees you charge are separate: a 90/10 split, collected into
    your own Stripe account. Upgrade from
    <a href="https://home.elevenmessenger.com">your home page</a>; payment
    happens on Stripe’s page, so we never see your card, name, or email.
  </p>
</section>

